## KPI Definition Workflow

Define campaign KPIs:

- [ ] 1. **Business alignment**: Map media KPIs to business objectives for {{client_name}} (revenue, leads, awareness lift)
- [ ] 2. **KPI hierarchy**: Structure KPIs at campaign, channel, and ad set levels
- [ ] 3. **Primary vs. secondary**: Distinguish primary KPIs (optimization targets) from secondary (monitoring metrics)
- [ ] 4. **Target setting**: Set targets based on industry benchmarks and historical data for {{industry}}
- [ ] 5. **Attribution model**: Select attribution model (last-click, linear, data-driven, marketing mix model)
- [ ] 6. **Reporting framework**: Define reporting cadence, dashboards, and escalation triggers
- [ ] 7. **Optimization triggers**: Set thresholds that trigger budget reallocation or creative changes

## Key Inputs
- Client: {{client_name}}
- Industry: {{industry}}
- Campaign objective: {{campaign_objective}}
- Channels: {{channels}}
- Budget: {{budget}}
